area_note               =\n| elevation_footnotes     =\n| elevation_m             =\n| elevation_max_m         =\n| population_footnotes    = <ref name=cubaone>{{cite web|title=Lugar que ocupa el territorio seg\u00fan la superficie y la poblaci\u00f3n|url=http://www.one.cu/publicaciones/08informacion/2010unamiradaacuba/03Cuba.pdf|work=Una MIRADA a Cuba|publisher=Oficina Nacional de Estad\u00edsticas. Cuba|language=Spanish|year=2010}}</ref> \n| population_total        = 1047015\n| population_as_of        = 2010-12-31\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      =\n| population_note         =\n| timezone1               = [[Eastern Time Zone (North America)|EST]]\n| utc_offset1             = -5\n| timezone1_DST           =\n| utc_offset1_DST         =\n| postal_code_type        =\n| postal_code             =\n| area_code_type          = \n| area_code               = +53-226\n| iso_code                =\n| website                 = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n'''Santiago de Cuba Province''' is the second most populated province in the island of [[Cuba]]. The largest city [[Santiago de Cuba]] is the main administrative center. Other large cities include [[Palma Soriano]], [[Contramaestre, Cuba|Contramaestre]], [[San Luis, Santiago de Cuba|San Luis]] and [[La Maya, Cuba|Songo-la Maya]].\n\n==History==\nSantiago de Cuba province has been the site of many [[battle]]s, both during the war for independence and the 1959 [[Cuban Revolution]], where much of the [[guerrilla warfare|guerrilla]] fighting took place in the mountainous province.\n\nPrior to 1976, Cuba was divided into six [[Provinces of Cuba#History|historical provinces]]. One of these was [[Oriente Province|Oriente]] province, which was, prior to 1905, known as Santiago de Cuba province. The present day province comprises the south-central region of Oriente.\n\n==Economy==\nThe province is rich in material resources such as [[iron]] and [[nickel]]. The economy, however, relies mostly on [[agriculture]], with large plantations growing [[banana]]s, [[Cocoa bean|cacao]], and [[coffee]] dotting the landscape. Industry is growing around the capital, as is [[tourism]]. The natural environment of the province attracts tourists from elsewhere in Cuba and from overseas.{{fact|date=January 2019}}\n\n==Municipalities==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Municipality!!Population<br />(2004)!!Area<br />(km\u00b2)!!Location!!Remarks\n|-\n|[[Contramaestre, Cuba|Contramaestre]]||{{commas|105493}}||{{commas|610.3}}||<small>{{Coord|20|18|0|N|76|15|2|W|format=dec|name=Contramaestre}}</small>||\n|-\n|[[Guam\u00e1, Cuba|Guam\u00e1]]||{{commas|35516}}||{{commas|965}}||<small>{{Coord|19|58|34|N|76|24|35|W|format=dec|name=Chivirico}}</small>||  [[Chivirico]]\n|-\n|[[Mella, Cuba|Mella]]||{{commas|33667}}||{{commas|335.2}}||<small>{{Coord|20|22|10|N|75|54|39|W|format=dec|name=Mella}}</small>||\n|-\n|[[Palma Soriano, Cuba|Palma Soriano]]||{{commas|124585}}||{{commas|845.8}}||<small>{{Coord|20|12|51|N|75|59|30|W|format=dec|name=Palma Soriano}}</small>||\n|-\n|[[San Luis, Santiago de Cuba|San Luis]]||{{commas|88496}}||{{commas|765}}||<small>{{Coord|20|11|17|N|75|50|55|W|format=dec|name=San Luis}}</small>||\n|-\n|[[Santiago de Cuba, Cuba|Santiago de Cuba]]||{{commas|472255}}||{{commas|1023.8}}||<small>{{Coord|20|02|25|N|75|48|53|W|format=dec|name=Santiago de Cuba}}</small>|| Provincial capital\n|-\n|[[Segundo Frente, Cuba|Segundo Frente]]||{{commas|40885}}||{{commas|540}}||<small>{{Coord|20|24|43|N|75|31|43|W|format=dec|name=Mayar\u00ed Arriba}}</small>||  [[Mayar\u00ed Arriba]]\n|-\n|[[Songo-La Maya, Cuba|Songo-La Maya]]||{{commas|100287}}||{{commas|721}}||<small>{{Coord|20|10|24|N|75|38|46|W|format=dec|name=La Maya}}</small>||  [[La Maya, Cuba|La Maya]]\n|-\n|[[Tercer Frente, Cuba|Tercer Frente]]||{{commas|30457}}||{{commas|364}}||<small>{{Coord|20|10|19|N|76|19|38|W|format=dec|name=Cruce de los Ba\u00f1os}}</small>||  [[Cruce de los Ba\u00f1os]]\n|}\n{{GeoGroupTemplate}}\n:''Source: Population from 2004 Census.''<ref name=atenas>{{Cite web| url=http://www.atenas.inf.cu/todo/Estadisticas/TABLA%20No_3balance.htm| title=2004 Population trends, by Province and Municipality| author= Atenas.cu| year= 2004| accessdate=2007-10-06 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070927111826/http://www.atenas.inf.cu/todo/Estadisticas/TABLA+No_3balance.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-27|language=es}}</ref> ''Area from 1976 municipal re-distribution.''<ref name=statoids>{{Cite web|url=http://www.statoids.com/ycu.html|title=Municipios of Cuba|author=Statoids|date=July 2003| accessdate=2007-10-06}}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\nIn 2004, the province of Santiago De Cuba had a population of 1,043,202.<ref name=atenas /> With a total area of {{convert|6156.44|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}},<ref name=census2002>{{Cite web| url=http://www.cubagob.cu/otras_info/censo/tablas_html/ii_4.htm| title=Population by Province| author= Government of Cuba| year= 2002| accessdate=2007-10-05|language=es}}</ref> the province had a population density of {{convert|169.4|/km2|/sqmi|abbr=on}}.\n\n==International relations==\n{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in Caribbean#Cuba|l1=List of twin towns and sister cities in Cuba}}\n\n===Twin towns \u2014 Sister cities===\nSantiago de Cuba Province is [[Twin towns and sister cities|twinned]] with:\n*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Naples]], Italy<ref name=\"Naples twinnings\">{{cite web|url=http://www.comune.napoli.it/flex/cm/pages/ServeBLOB.php/L/IT/IDPagina/5931|title= Comune di Napoli -Gemellaggi|accessdate=2013-08-08|last=Vacca|first=Maria Luisa|work=Comune di Napoli|trans-title=Naples - Twin Towns|language= Italian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130722204102/http://www.comune.napoli.it/flex/cm/pages/ServeBLOB.php/L/IT/IDPagina/5931|archivedate=2013-07-22 }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Cuba}}\n*[[Oriente Province]]\n*[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Cubao]]\n*[[Father Jos\u00e9 Conrado]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Santiago de Cuba Province}}\n*[http://www.santiago.cu/ Santiago.cu (in Spanish)]\n*[http://www.santiago-de-cuba.net/ Travel info on Santiago de Cuba]\n*[http://www.santiagoencuba.com/ santiagoencuba.com (in Spanish)]\n*[http://www.santiagodecubacity.org/ Santiago de Cuba City (in English and Spanish)]\n\n{{Provinces of Cuba|province=Santiago de Cuba}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Santiago De Cuba Province}}\n[[Category:Santiago de Cuba Province| ]]\n[[Category:Provinces of Cuba]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1976]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Province of Cuba}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = Santiago de Cuba Province\n| native_name             =\n| native_name_lang        = <!-- ISO 639-2 code e.g. \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} instead -->\n| settlement_type         = [[Provinces of Cuba|Province]] of [[Cuba]]\n| image_skyline           =\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           =\n| image_flag              = Bandera de la Provincia Santiago de Cuba.png\n| image_shield            = Escudo de la Provincia Santiago de Cuba.png\n| nickname                =\n| motto                   =\n| image_map               = Santiago de Cuba in Cuba.svg\n| map_alt                 =\n| map_caption             =\n| pushpin_map             =\n| pushpin_label_position  =\n| pushpin_map_alt         =\n| pushpin_map_caption     =\n| coordinates             = {{coord|20|12|N|75|55|W|type:adm1st_region:CU|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint           =\n| coordinates_footnotes   =\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[Cuba]]\n| subdivision_type1       =\n| subdivision_name1       =\n| subdivision_type2       =\n| subdivision_name2       =\n| subdivision_type3       =\n| subdivision_name3       =\n| established_title       =\n| e